etermining the best pricing policy for the product, considering high development costs and a five-year life cycle. Demand is highly responsive to price changes, and the company has patented the technology to prevent competition for two years.\"", "\"MARGINAL COST CALCULATION\":\"The marginal cost for each air conditioning unit, after adjusting the labour cost, is calculated to be $49.90.\"", "\"OPTIMUM PRICE AND QUANTITY\":\"The optimum price and quantity to maximize profits are determined by equating marginal revenue to marginal cost. The optimum price is $400, and the optimum quantity is 23,337 units.\"", "\"PENETRATION PRICING STRATEGY\":\"Penetration pricing involves initially charging a low price to attract customers and gain market share quickly.\"", "\"MARKET SKIMMING STRATEGY\":\"Market skimming involves setting a high price initially to maximize profits from early adopters before gradually lowering the price.\"", "\"PENETRATION PRICING\":\"Penetration pricing involves setting a low initial price to attract a large number of buyers and gain a significant market share. This strategy is suitable when demand is highly elastic, economies of scale can be achieved, new entrants are discouraged, or the company wants to quickly move through the product life cycle stages.\"", "\"STRATEGIC PRICING AND REVENUE OPTIMIZATION FOR ALG CO\u2019S NEW PRODUCT LAUNCH\":\"ALG Co is launching a new product with a three-year life expectancy. The company aims to set the right price to recover high development costs. Market research indicates that demand decreases by 2,000 units for every $2 increase in price and increases by 2,000 units for every $2 decrease. The demand curve is expressed as P = 310 - 0.001Q.\"", "\"DEMAND CURVE FORMULA\":\"The demand curve formula used in the case: P = 310 - 0.001Q, where P is the price and Q is the quantity demanded.\"", "\"REVENUE MAXIMIZATION\":\"Revenue maximization occurs where marginal revenue equals zero. This is the point at which any additional unit sold would not increase total revenue.\"", "\"PRICING STRATEGY AND PROFIT MAXIMIZATION FOR TR CO\u2019S PARAPAIN AND NEW ANTI-MALARIA DRUG\":\"TR Co is a pharmaceutical company reviewing its pricing policy for Parapain, a pain relief drug, after its patent expired and competitors entered the market. The company is also launching a new anti-malaria drug with a patent, expected to save millions of lives. The case involves determining the optimal pricing strategy for Parapain and understanding the implications of market competition and production costs.\"", "\"PARAPAIN\":\"Parapain is a pain relief drug used for the treatment of headaches. TR Co had a patent on Parapain, which has now expired, allowing competitors to enter the market with similar products.\"", "\"NEW ANTI-MALARIA DRUG\":\"TR Co's new anti-malaria drug is a revolutionary product expected to save millions of lives. The drug has a patent, and no similar drug exists in the market. The launch is eagerly anticipated worldwide.\"", "\"ANTI-MALARIA DRUG\":TR Co's new and unique anti-malaria drug, which cost millions of dollars to develop and has obtained a patent, is expected to save millions of lives. There are no similar drugs currently available in the market, making this drug particularly significant. Although the demand levels are unknown, the launch is eagerly anticipated worldwide. The anti-malaria drug is also used as an example to illustrate the application of penetration pricing and market skimming pricing strategies, due to its unique characteristics and patented status, making it suitable for market skimming."], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}